## 16. **src/plugin-sdk/core.ts** (Key plugin SDK functions)

**`defineChannelPluginEntry(options)`**: Creates a plugin entry that registers a channel capability
- Options: `id`, `name`, `description`, `plugin`, `configSchema`, `setRuntime`, `registerCliMetadata`, `registerFull`
- Handles both "cli-metadata" and "full" registration modes
- Returns `DefinedChannelPluginEntry` with register function

**`defineSetupPluginEntry(plugin)`**: Minimal setup-entry helper that exports `{ plugin }`

**`createChatChannelPlugin(params)`**: Higher-level builder for chat-style channels
- `params.base`: Core chat plugin config (id, meta, setup, capabilities, config, etc.)
- `params.security`: DM security (optional, can use shorthand or full adapter)
- `params.pairing`: Text pairing (shorthand with idLabel, message, notify)
- `params.threading`: Reply mode (shorthand or custom resolver)
- `params.outbound`: Send behavior (base config + attachedResults helpers)
- Returns fully composed `ChannelPlugin`

**`getChatChannelMeta(channelId)`**: Gets default metadata for a channel

